post_text:
Good afternoon Topock School families,

We are excited to announce our online schooling begins tomorrow, Thursday, August 6th. We will also be providing breakfast and lunch for students daily and will be available for pick up from 8 a.m. to 10 a.m. Any parents that have not signed up for food service and would like to be added to the list please call the office 928-768-3344 and leave a message. Food will only be provided for students currently enrolled at Topock School. If your child has an IEP, you will be contacted by school personnel to discuss how services such as speech will be provided. All students' work will be graded this year. Therefore, it‚Äôs imperative that students participate fully with the online instruction, turn in all assignments and give 100% effort. We are all going to do our best to make this an outstanding school year in spite of the obstacles we are currently dealing with. We will have more information available on our school website and Facebook page as soon as it's available. Thanks everyone. Let's have an awesome school year!

post_text:
Dear Topock School Families,

I just finished watching Governor Ducey's live briefing. Many of us were anticipating an update or his guidance on the school closure currently in place until August 17th. The Governor stated he will provide an update next week regarding his current executive order. That being said, we WILL begin on-line instruction Thursday August 6th. We also anticipate resuming our school breakfast and lunch program on August 6th as well. Prior to the start of school August 6th, Topock School staff will be contacting our families to set up appointments for students to pick up their chromebooks, complete registration, perform some base level testing, and meet their teacher. At this point in time ALL people on campus, staff, parents, and students, will be required to wear facemasks. (cloth facemasks are acceptable) Social distancing will be maintained, and ample hand sanitizer will be available.

Our start date for on-line instruction is firm. However, pending the Governor's news conference next week, some other things may change.

post_text:
Dear Topock School Parents,

This afternoon the Governor and the state School Superintendent announced that the school closure has been extended until April 10th.

That being said, the Teachers will be meeting with me Monday morning to discuss how best to move forward to educate our students. I would like to implement online instruction as soon as possible. To do so I need to know who has internet access and who does not for all Kindergarten through 6th grade students. Please email me at jwarren@topockschool.com and let me know if you do or do not have internet access at home. This will assist the teaching staff to make the best plans moving forward.

Packets of school work for those that requested them will be available for pick-up on Monday along with meals starting at 10AM.

Thank you, and enjoy your weekend.

John Warren
Superintendent
Topock ESD #12
Past President Arizona Rural Schools Association
"Go For Excellence!"

"If your actions inspire others to dream more, learn more, do more, and become more, you are a leader."
-Chris Ledoux

Governor Doug Ducey is with Superintendent Kathy Hoffman and Arizona Department of Education.
March 15 at 4:14 PM ¬∑

We‚Äôre joining together to keep Arizona‚Äôs kids, families, and school communities safe and healthy. Arizona is united, and we‚Äôll get through this. Superintendent Kathy Hoffman

This decision is not made lightly, but it is the right thing to do to bring certainty and consistency to all Arizona schools. With schools closing, we are working together to provide assistance during this time and lessen the impact on all Arizona families.

It‚Äôs important for families & parents to know that while this will address operational issues, closing schools will not stop the spread of #COVID19. It is the recommendation of public health officials that kids who are not at school remain at home to the greatest extent possible.

For more information on ways to stay safe and healthy, visit http://azhealth.gov.

Read our full letter here: https://azgovernor.gov/governor/blog/2020/03/open-letter-arizona-families-educators-school-leaders-and-education-community
